not full-time damage control.

183
00:09:48,220 --> 00:09:51,130
所以我们要让加勒特回到正轨
Which is why we have to put Garrett back on his feet.

184
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:54,220
你是想让他脱轨吧  弗兰克
You want him on his ass, Frank.

185
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:56,350
是总统这么跟你说的吗
Is this what the president told you?

186
00:09:57,310 --> 00:09:59,180
他现在太多疑了  凯茜
He's paranoid, Cathy.

187
00:09:59,180 --> 00:10:02,100
他想让大家跟我反目
He's trying to turn people against me.

188
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:04,230
是你自己的行为让大家跟你反目
You're turning them against yourself.

189
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:07,490
你在要求我坑害总统
You're asking me to undermine the president.

190
00:10:12,610 --> 00:10:13,680
好吧
All right.

191
00:10:16,530 --> 00:10:22,660
假如总统对我的指责属实
Let's say that what the President has accused me of is true.

192
00:10:24,140 --> 00:10:25,550
这就真的很糟吗
Would that be so bad?

193
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:28,480
考虑一下这么做的结果
If taken to its conclusion?

194
00:10:29,350 --> 00:10:31,880
