Wouldn't the country?

196
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:37,880
我不想牵扯进去
I don't want anything to do with this.

197
00:10:37,880 --> 00:10:40,420
就再做一次  凯茜
Just one more time, Cathy.

198
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:43,360
别去管那些条条框框
Let's unshackle ourselves.

199
00:10:45,530 --> 00:10:48,030
机会只有一次  冯先生
This is a one-time offer, Mr. Feng.

200
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:51,710
我要白纸黑字写下来  不加任何条件
I would need it in writing. Open-ended, no restrictions.

201
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:53,440
法定豁免权也是一样
The same goes for legal immunity.

202
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,030
首先我要确认
First I need to know whether or not

203
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:57,270
你是否通过拉尼根的赌场洗钱
you funneled money through Lanagin's casino.

204
00:10:57,270 --> 00:11:00,050
不  等我安全抵达美国
No, no. I will speak freely once I've arrived safely

205
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:01,260
我才会全盘托出
in the United States.

206
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:03,260
除非你现在就能提供确凿证据
Unless you provide valuable evidence now,

207
00:11:03,270 --> 00:11:06,760
司法部长不会答应任何豁免权
the attorney general will not grant immunity on any level.

208
00:11:07,460 --> 00:11:09,640
我在中国已经全部否认了这些指控
I've denied these allegations in China.

209
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:11,400
我的敌人想置我于死地
My enemies want me dead.

210
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,470
你这是逼我给他们证据
You're asking me to give them confirmation.

211
00:11:13,470 --> 00:11:15,990
作为回报  我们会给你提供避难所
And we're giving you safe haven in return.

212
00:11:15,990 --> 00:11:17,960
我在迪拜已经有避难所了
I already have safe haven in Dubai.

213
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:20,120
你在那里的庇护所只是暂时的
Your asylum there is only temporary.

214
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:22,690
我们给你提供的是永久身份
We're offering you permanent status.

215
00:11:23,110 --> 00:11:25,700
我相信他们也会给我永久身份
I'm confident that they will grant me permanent status.

216
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:28,750
是外交部长亲口跟你说的吗
Did you hear that directly from the Minister of Foreign Affairs?

217
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:30,710
因为我刚跟他谈过
Because I just spoke to him.

218
00:11:31,470 --> 00:11:34,080
现在你连护照都没有
Right now you are a man without a passport.

219
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:36,970
北京方面还没查封的资产
Whatever assets Beijing hasn't seized

220
00:11:36,970 --> 00:11:41,020
也都被所有和中美关系紧密的国家冻结了
are frozen in every country with close ties to the United Sates or China,

221
00:11:41,020 --> 00:11:44,360
那基本上是全世界所有国家
which is just about every country in the world.

222
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:49,160
你想要自由和金钱  我们想要信息
You want your freedom and fortune. We want information.

223
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:53,060
冯先生
Mr. Feng?

224
00:11:54,530 --> 00:11:55,790
你想知道什么
What do you need to know?

225
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:59,690
向我证实确实有洗钱行为
Confirm for me the existence of a money-laundering scheme.

226
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:05,700
是的  我们用赌场来掩饰外国献金
Yes. We used the casino to mask foreign contributions.

227
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:10,200
好的
All right.

228
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:14,270
你们中谁跟我讲讲这是怎么回事
One of you want to tell me what this is all about?

229
00:12:15,460 --> 00:12:16,640
你必须得遵从
You have to comply.

230
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,240
你是说我得出席
You mean I have to show up.

231
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:20,210
除非我们上诉
Unless we appeal.

232
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:21,390
我们会输
We'd lose.

233
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:23,100
她要不是证据确凿
She wouldn't have issued the subpoena

234
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:25,040
也不会传唤我
unless she had something substantial.

235
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:25,750
我同意
I agree.

236
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:27,230
所以我觉得你该去
Which is why I think you should go

237
00:12:27,230 --> 00:12:28,480
并拒不解释
and plead the Fifth.

238
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,770
你觉得她手上有什么
What do you think she has?

239
00:12:29,770 --> 00:12:31,320
我不想妄加推断
I don't want to speculate.

240
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,930
老天  我付给你们六个一天的钱
God damn it, I pay the six of you more in one day

241
00:12:33,930 --> 00:12:36,000
比供个孩子上大学都多
than it costs to put a kid through college.

242
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:37,870
我请你们是要你们比我知道得多
And I pay you to know more than I do.

243
00:12:37,870 --> 00:12:39,970
她问询时说的对我们会很有帮助
Her line of questioning will tell us a lot.

244
00:12:39,970 --> 00:12:43,340
万一她真要提出指控  我们可以据此准备辩护
We can use that to prepare our defense in case there's an indictment.

245
00:12:44,690 --> 00:12:45,890
我什么时候走
When do I have to go?

246
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:48,080
你的会面是在后天
Your interview is the day after next.

247
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:50,270
48小时
48 hours?

248
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,250
发动不了吗
Having trouble starting it?

249
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,650
是的  可能电池没电了吧
Yeah. I think the battery might be dead.

250
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:32,920
如果你想试试跨接启动  我有电线
I have some cables if you want to try and jump it.

251
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:35,310
这真的不麻烦吗
You sure you don't mind?

252
00:13:35,310 --> 00:13:36,600
一点也不
Not at all.

253
00:13:37,770 --> 00:13:39,590
好吧  你真是太好了
All right. It's really nice of you.

254
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:41,160
开引擎盖  我把我车开过来
Pop your hood. I'll bring my car around.

255
00:13:41,170 --> 00:13:42,300
好
Sure.

256
00:13:45,350 --> 00:13:47,880
这位是彼得  他开车送我回来的
This is Peter. He's the guy who drove me back.

257
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:50,420
这些要放哪
Where do you want these?

258
00:13:50,420 --> 00:13:52,510
我来拿  谢谢
I'll take 'em. Thanks.

259
00:13:54,460 --> 00:13:55,700
瑞秋  是吗
Rachel, right?

260
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:57,500
是的
Yeah.

261
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:59,040
丽萨说你俩是室友
Lisa said you two were roommates.

262
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,010
要我给你拿点什么  来杯水吗
Can I get you something? A glass of water?

263
00:14:01,010 --> 00:14:02,930
不用  谢谢  我得走了
No, thanks. I should really get going.

264
00:14:02,930 --> 00:14:04,470
好吧  太谢谢你了
All right. I can't thank you enough.

265
00:14:04,470 --> 00:14:06,160
不客气  希望车能修好
My pleasure. Good luck with the car.

266
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,040
谢谢
Thanks.

267
00:14:07,260 --> 00:14:09,780
希望只是电池没电  晚安
I hope it's only a dead battery. Have a good night.

268
00:14:11,940 --> 00:14:13,180
我们应该给他些钱
We should give him some money.

269
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,450
彼得
Peter.

270
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:21,700
她得离开
She needs to be gone.

271
00:14:23,820 --> 00:14:25,140
你跟我说她可以留下的
Y-- you told me she could stay.

272
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:26,520
我改主意了
I changed my mind.

273
00:14:26,570 --> 00:14:28,390
你说你不在乎她在不在这儿
But you said you didn't care if she was here --

274
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:30,550
我不需要解释什么
I don't need to explain myself.

275
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:33,870
你受不了了  是吗
You can't stand it, can you?

276
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:36,200
受不了我爱上了别人
The idea that I might actually love somebody.

277
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:38,660
受不了我生命中除了你还有别人
That I might have somebody in my life who isn't you.

278
00:14:38,660 --> 00:14:41,370
如果你在乎她  就让她走  瑞秋
If you care about her, make it happen, Rachel.

279
00:14:43,630 --> 00:14:44,630
没事吧
Is everything okay?

280
00:14:44,630 --> 00:14:46,990
没事  告诉你朋友我不会要钱的
Yeah. You need to tell your friend that I won't take any money.

281
00:14:46,990 --> 00:14:48,260
我很乐意帮忙
I was happy to do it.

282
00:14:48,260 --> 00:14:50,410
我们都需要好心人帮忙
We all need a good Samaritan every now and again.

283
00:14:55,910 --> 00:14:57,350
麦金尼斯将军被判处
Did you feel justice was served

284
00:14:57,350 --> 00:14:59,950
四十年有期徒刑时  你觉得正义得到伸张了吗
when General McGinnis got sentenced to 40 years?

285
00:14:59,950 --> 00:15:01,630
就他的罪行而言  正义是得以伸张了
Yes, as far as his crimes go.

286
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:03,050
但还有成千的服役士兵没有...
But not for thousands of servicemen and --

287
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:04,830
抱歉  抱歉打断你的讲话
I'm -- I'm sor-- I'm sorry to interrupt.

288
00:15:05,130 --> 00:15:06,840
我的制作人告诉我
m-- my producer is telling me that,

289
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:08,820
杰奎琳·夏普刚打电话来
Jacqueline Sharp has called in,

290
00:15:08,820 --> 00:15:12,230
众议院多数党党鞭  议员女士  你在吗
the house majority whip. C-- congresswoman, are you there?

291
00:15:12,230 --> 00:15:14,880
是的  我在  克里斯  谢谢你接我的电话
Yes, I'm here, Chris. And thank you for taking my call.

292
00:15:15,190 --> 00:15:16,320
谢谢你
Thank you.

293
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:17,570
你好  梅根
Hello, Megan.

294
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:19,020
议员女士
Congresswoman.

295
00:15:19,020 --> 00:15:20,690
首先  作为一名老兵
First of all, as a veteran like yourself,

296
00:15:20,690 --> 00:15:23,340
我想感谢你对国家的贡献
I want to thank you for your service to our country.

297
00:15:23,340 --> 00:15:25,110
这是责任  无需感谢
Duty doesn't require thanks.

298
00:15:25,210 --> 00:15:26,890
我很高兴你提到责任这个话题
I'm glad you brought up duty,

299
00:15:26,890 --> 00:15:30,680
因为你最近将它称之为洗脑
because you recently equated it with brainwashing.

300
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:31,870
那不是我的本意
That's not what I meant.

301
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:34,350
你说"紧跟党派路线"
You said "Toeing the party line."

302
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:37,230
我的本意是文化和体系是...
What I meant was that the culture and the system is one that --

303
00:15:37,230 --> 00:15:39,020
我不是打电话来和你辩论的  梅根  恰恰相反
I didn't call to argue with you, Megan. The opposite.

304
00:15:39,020 --> 00:15:42,640
我们要解决这个问题  就必须找到共同点
We can't fix this problem until we find some common ground.

305
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:43,520
你不觉得吗
Wouldn't you agree?

306
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:45,560
就我来看这个问题没有妥协空间
There is no middle ground as far as I'm concerned.

307
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:46,280
军队需要改变
The military needs to change --

308
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:48,380
你和我都曾经在军中服役
Can't we agree that you and I served

309
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:50,750
以保护人民自由辩论的权利
so that we could protect open debate,

310
00:15:50,780 --> 00:15:53,070
而这正是民主的基础  你说不是吗
which is the very bedrock of democracy?

311
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:55,280
理论上是的  但这不是我要说的
Yes, in theory, but that's not what I'm talking about.

312
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:57,330
不是理论上  是实际上
Not in theory. In reality.

313
00:15:57,330 --> 00:16:00,280
勇敢的人为了这份自由不惜牺牲生命
Brave men and women die fighting for that freedom.

314
00:16:00,290 --> 00:16:03,690
勇敢的涵义就是为那些和你意见相左的人
The meaning of bravery is fighting for the freedom

315
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:05,710
也同样享有自由而战斗
of those with whom you disagree.

316
00:16:05,710 --> 00:16:07,350
当然  但我们回到真正的话题上来好吗
Sure, but let's get back to the issue here.

317
00:16:07,350 --> 00:16:10,630
我认为不勇敢的人是克莱尔·安德伍德
What I don't think is brave is Claire Underwood

318
00:16:10,630 --> 00:16:14,180
逃避这场辩论  找你替她进行这场斗争
dodging this debate and having you fight this battle for her instead.

319
00:16:14,180 --> 00:16:15,360
不是这样的
That's not true.

320
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:19,160
那我为什么在和你而不是她谈话  这是她的法案
Then why am I talking to you instead of her? It's her bill.

321
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:20,960
不只是她  是我们共同的成果
It's not just hers. It's all of ours.

322
00:16:20,970 --> 00:16:23,790
可是你勇敢地说出来了
Except one of you is brave enough to say it,

323
00:16:23,790 --> 00:16:25,690
而她却是个懦夫
and the other is a coward.

324
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:27,490
安德伍德夫人勇敢地
Mrs. Underwood was brave enough

325
00:16:27,490 --> 00:16:29,740
在全国电视节目上承认她...
to go on national television and admit that she --

326
00:16:29,740 --> 00:16:31,440
没错  但那之后她去哪了
Yeah, and where has she been since then?

327
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:34,170
应付丑闻  躲避媒体
Deflecting scandal and hiding from the press.

328
00:16:34,420 --> 00:16:37,520
梅根  你在《纽约时代杂志》上说我可耻
You called me disgraceful in The New York Times, Megan,

329
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:39,160
你当然有这个权利
and you have every right.

330
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:42,960
但我也有权说  安德伍德夫人是可耻的
But I also have the right to say that Mrs. Underwood is disgraceful,

331
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,410
因为没有什么
because there is nothing

332
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:47,400
比当逃兵更可耻
more disgraceful than running from a battle.

333
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:53,430
-梅根  -我们根本没有...
- Megan? - That is -- we're not even...

334
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:56,940
我们马上回来
We'll be right back.

335
00:17:00,290 --> 00:17:01,470
你要去哪
Where are you going?

336
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:03,040
去国会
To the Capitol.

337
00:17:04,950 --> 00:17:07,630
冯提到我或总统了吗
Did Feng mention either me or the president?

338
00:17:07,630 --> 00:17:08,660
邓巴不肯说
Dunbar wouldn't say.

339
00:17:08,660 --> 00:17:11,180
但冯确认了洗钱行为
But the fact that Feng confirmed the money laundering

340
00:17:11,180 --> 00:17:13,020
