几乎肯定是会的
It most definitely will.

850
00:42:00,450 --> 00:42:01,950
我不那么肯定
I'm not sure about that.

851
00:42:01,950 --> 00:42:03,450
你们看了总统的声明了吗
Did you see the president's address?

852
00:42:03,450 --> 00:42:04,250
我们看了
We did.

853
00:42:04,250 --> 00:42:06,230
我觉得能起些作用  控制事态
I think it will help. Stop the bleeding.

854
00:42:06,230 --> 00:42:08,370
而且弹劾可以被否决
Impeachment can be defeated.

855
00:42:08,870 --> 00:42:11,070
但那是我们要避免的
But that's we need to avoid.

856
00:42:12,430 --> 00:42:14,090
你希望弹劾
You want impeachment...

857
00:42:14,090 --> 00:42:16,060
为什么要打一场明知会输的仗
Why fight a losing battle?

858
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:19,040
我们在众议院是多数党
We have a majority in the House.

859
00:42:19,040 --> 00:42:20,060
现在是
We do now.

860
00:42:20,070 --> 00:42:24,140
但如果本党不能和一个污点总统划清界限
But if this party fails to distance itself from a toxic president...

861
00:42:24,890 --> 00:42:26,540
我们在做长远打算
We're thinking ahead here.

862
00:42:26,650 --> 00:42:29,130
所以我才会找你就法案的事和解
It's why I came to you about the bill.

863
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:31,320
我们不值得为它翻脸
Because it wasn't worth burning a bridge over.

864
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:35,630
长远来讲  我们合作的好处更多
In the long run we have a lot more to gain by working together.

865
00:42:35,870 --> 00:42:36,910
我不明白
I don't understand.

866
00:42:36,910 --> 00:42:38,660
你在《电讯报》采访的时候说你会
You said in the Telegraph article that you would sta--

867
00:42:38,670 --> 00:42:39,970
我必须那么说
I had to.

868
00:42:39,970 --> 00:42:42,350
我的办公室跟总统的只隔了三个房间
My office is three doors down from the president's.

869
00:42:42,350 --> 00:42:44,410
我不能公开诋毁他
I can't publicly deride him.

870
00:42:46,350 --> 00:42:47,870
你要我来
You want me to do it?

871
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:54,790
我们想要你做你最拿手的  拉选票
We want you to do what you do so well: whip the votes.

872
00:43:04,610 --> 00:43:06,390
我不能背叛总统
I can't abandon the president.

873
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:08,400
如果本党救了他
If the party rescues him,

874
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:11,400
我们将在中期选举时失去50个席位
we'll lose 50 seats in the House in the midterms.

875
00:43:11,400 --> 00:43:14,080
你会失去你在领导层的地位
You will lose your position in the leadership.

876
00:43:14,080 --> 00:43:15,550
我们要花十年
And it will take us a decade

877
00:43:15,550 --> 00:43:18,350
重新赢得选民的信任
to regain the trust of the electorate.

878
00:43:18,380 --> 00:43:21,260
我们只求你肯听取意见
All we're asking is that you have an open mind.

879
00:43:21,260 --> 00:43:22,660
克莱尔就是如此
Claire kept an open mind,

880
00:43:22,660 --> 00:43:26,090
你得以修改性侵法案
and you'll pass sexual assault reform as a result.

881
00:43:26,090 --> 00:43:28,320
你不能把弹劾和...
You can't possibly compare impeachment to --

882
00:43:28,320 --> 00:43:29,920
只是举个例子  杰姬
It's an illustration, Jackie.

883
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:32,140
说明未来会怎么样
Of what the future looks like.

884
00:43:33,120 --> 00:43:36,320
我们提出的  是进步
What we offer is progress.

885
00:43:36,840 --> 00:43:39,530
并保证日后还会有更多进步
With a promise of more to come.

886
00:43:41,990 --> 00:43:44,020
这只是个开始  杰姬
It's only the beginning, Jackie.

887
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:48,060
坚决  务实  记得吗
Ruthless pragmatism, remember?

888
00:43:48,130 --> 00:43:49,970
所以我才选你做党鞭
That's why I wanted you to be the whip.

889
00:43:49,970 --> 00:43:53,060
我们三个是同一类人
The three of us, we're cut from the same cloth.

890
00:43:56,260 --> 00:43:57,790
副总统先生
Mr. Vice President,

891
00:43:59,380 --> 00:44:03,020
你要我做的  几乎是叛国
what you're asking is just shy of treason.

892
00:44:05,140 --> 00:44:08,820
几乎  也就是政治
Just shy. Which is politics.

893
00:44:12,420 --> 00:44:14,230
小心  那很易碎
Be careful. It's delicate.

894
00:44:17,330 --> 00:44:18,470
这是什么
What is it?

895
00:44:19,310 --> 00:44:22,310
一件我做了很久的事
Something I've been working on for a very long time.

896
00:44:23,050 --> 00:44:24,740
马上就要完成了
And it's nearly finished.

897
00:44:26,150 --> 00:44:27,320
杰姬
Jackie?

898
00:44:29,180 --> 00:44:30,600
帮我们完成吧
Help us finish it.

